592
00:30:23,344 --> 00:30:24,896
Well, if you wanna get
some of those points back,

593
00:30:24,965 --> 00:30:26,758
you're gonna have to
start participating.

594
00:30:26,827 --> 00:30:29,448
[CJ] Maybe she thinks
she's too good for us.

595
00:30:29,517 --> 00:30:31,620
[Counselor]
Is that true, Laura?

596
00:30:31,689 --> 00:30:32,724
No.

597
00:30:32,793 --> 00:30:34,896
Look at her. You can tell.

598
00:30:34,965 --> 00:30:36,000
I knew girls
like you in school.

599
00:30:36,068 --> 00:30:37,689
Stuck up rich kids.

600
00:30:37,758 --> 00:30:39,620
Maybe she just hasn't
got anything to say.

601
00:30:39,689 --> 00:30:42,413
Give her a couple of
drinks, she'll loosen up.

602
00:30:42,482 --> 00:30:43,896
Laura. Let me
ask you something.

603
00:30:43,965 --> 00:30:45,931
Why do you think you're in here?

604
00:30:46,000 --> 00:30:47,310
I don't know.

605
00:30:47,379 --> 00:30:50,206
Well, I'll tell you why, because
your parents put you here.

606
00:30:50,275 --> 00:30:51,862
Because you're making
their lives miserable,

607
00:30:51,931 --> 00:30:54,517
because your own life
has become unmanageable.

608
00:30:54,586 --> 00:30:56,551
You're an embarrassment to
your friends, your family,

609
00:30:56,620 --> 00:30:58,103
everybody around you.

610
00:30:58,172 --> 00:31:01,275
They may not say that to you,
but believe me, it's true.

611
00:31:01,344 --> 00:31:02,724
I mean, it's bad
enough for your parents

612
00:31:02,793 --> 00:31:03,586
