00:41:20,310 --> 00:41:21,724
But now all of a
sudden it's yesterday.

782
00:41:21,793 --> 00:41:24,965
"Anything you say, sir,"
Winslow's poster boy.

783
00:41:27,344 --> 00:41:29,034
So what about you?

784
00:41:29,103 --> 00:41:31,482
What about me?

785
00:41:31,551 --> 00:41:33,068
Why are you in here?

786
00:41:49,103 --> 00:41:50,586
Why'd you do that?

787
00:41:53,931 --> 00:41:55,310
I don't know.

788
00:41:55,379 --> 00:41:58,310
[chuckles nervously]

789
00:41:58,379 --> 00:42:00,620
Some days, I--

790
00:42:02,517 --> 00:42:05,896
Well, some days I get all
wired and I feel great.

791
00:42:05,965 --> 00:42:08,448
I feel like I could
jump out of an airplane

792
00:42:08,517 --> 00:42:12,517
without a parachute and just
fly for days, you know?

793
00:42:12,586 --> 00:42:15,103
And other days...
[laughs nervously]

794
00:42:20,655 --> 00:42:22,137
They call it bipolar.

795
00:42:22,206 --> 00:42:24,103
It's a...

796
00:42:24,172 --> 00:42:26,275
manic depressive, you know.

797
00:42:26,344 --> 00:42:28,793
But I'm much, much
better now really.

798
00:42:28,862 --> 00:42:31,965
I mean, they make me take the
meds here and they help a lot.

799
00:42:32,034 --> 00:42:33,034
So...

800
00:42:35,413 --> 00:42:37,965
Ha... I don't think I could
ever do that to myself.

801
00:42:40,896 --> 00:42:42,241
What about you?
Why are you in here?

802
00:42:44,344 --> 00:42:45,241
For being stupid.

803
00:42:59,310 --> 00:43:01,344
[Rachel] Come on, let's go.

804
00:43:03,379 --> 00:43:04,931
[Laura pants]

805
00:43:06,448 --> 00:43:07,724
Go, go.

806
00:43:11,862 --> 00:43:15,000
[suspenseful music]

807
00:43:20,034 --> 00:43:22,620
Go.

808
00:43:22,689 --> 00:43:23,758
[chair moves]

809
00:43:37,896 --> 00:43:38,896
[Rachel whispering]
You go first.

810
00:43:38,965 --> 00:43:40,137
[Laura] How come you are not?

811
00:43:40,206 --> 00:43:41,620
-[Rachel] You.
-[Laura] Okay.

812
00:43:54,413 --> 00:43:57,827
Rachel, it's a dead end.

813
00:43:57,896 --> 00:43:58,965
[Rachel] There she is.

814
00:43:59,034 --> 00:44:00,896
I followed her out here.

815
00:44:00,965 --> 00:44:02,862
She tried to escape.

816
00:44:02,931 --> 00:44:04,620
[panting]

817
00:44:04,689 --> 00:44:07,379
[Rachel] She tried to escape!

818
00:44:07,448 --> 00:44:09,000
[Security man]
We're not gonna hurt you.

819
00:44:09,068 --> 00:44:10,172
[Security woman]
Come on, stay right there.

820
00:44:10,241 --> 00:44:11,827
[Security man] Calm down,
we're not gonna hurt you.

821
00:44:11,896 --> 00:44:13,413
Calm down!
We won't hurt you!

822
00:44:13,482 --> 00:44:14,793
[Laura] Stay back!

823
00:44:17,241 --> 00:44:18,551
[Security man] Calm down!

824
00:44:18,620 --> 00:44:20,310
You go back to your room.

825
00:44:22,206 --> 00:44:24,517
[Laura panting]

826
00:44:28,482 --> 00:44:30,241
[panting]

827
00:44:58,413 --> 00:44:59,758
[Laura] No! Wait...

828
00:44:59,827 --> 00:45:01,172
[CJ shushing]
I'm on your side.

829
00:45:01,241 --> 00:45:02,862
[Laura] What are you doing?

830
00:45:07,448 --> 00:45:08,620
[Laura panting]

831
00:45:08,689 --> 00:45:09,793
Shut up and listen.

832
00:45:09,862 --> 00:45:10,896
When you get out
to the parking lot,

833
00:45:10,965 --> 00:45:11,896
head for the trees
on your right,

834
00:45:11,965 --> 00:45:13,379
don't stop till
you hit the road.

835
00:45:13,448 --> 00:45:15,758
Call a woman named Nora Fields.
You get the Teen Law Office.

836
00:45:15,827 --> 00:45:16,758
Tell her what you've
seen in here. Everything.

837
00:45:16,827 --> 00:45:17,793
You got that?

838
00:45:17,862 --> 00:45:20,448
Yeah, yeah.
Nora Fields, right.

839
00:45:20,517 --> 00:45:21,620
[CJ] Come on.

840
00:45:23,827 --> 00:45:25,034
[Laura] Wait, wait,
what about the doors?

841
00:45:25,103 --> 00:45:26,620
Just leave that to me.

842
00:45:29,413 --> 00:45:31,448
[Emergency bell rings]

843
00:45:31,517 --> 00:45:32,827
[CJ] Go, Go!

844
00:45:38,758 --> 00:45:39,793
[grunts]

845
00:45:48,448 --> 00:45:50,206
David, hi, its me.

846
00:45:50,275 --> 00:45:51,793
Now I know it's early.
I'm sorry.

847
00:45:51,862 --> 00:45:54,137
But I need
you to come pick me up.

848
00:45:54,206 --> 00:45:55,586
Eh-- It's a long story.

849
00:45:55,655 --> 00:45:56,965
I'll tell you when you get here.

850
00:46:09,344 --> 00:46:10,862
You sure you wanna do this?

851
00:46:10,931 --> 00:46:12,379
You can always stay
with me you know.

852
00:46:12,448 --> 00:46:13,965
No, everybody's
looking for me.

853
00:46:14,034 --> 00:46:15,758
I just want it all to be over.

854
00:46:20,413 --> 00:46:22,448
Hey, I'll call you later.

855
00:46:22,517 --> 00:46:25,137
Bye.

856
00:46:25,206 --> 00:46:27,000
Mum? Dad?

857
00:46:28,827 --> 00:46:30,241
[Michelle] Baby.

858
00:46:30,310 --> 00:46:31,482
You wouldn't believe
the terrible things--

859
00:46:31,551 --> 00:46:32,655
[Robert] Laura?

860
00:46:32,724 --> 00:46:35,517
They strapped us
in chairs and they...

861
00:46:35,586 --> 00:46:38,172
put straight jackets on
us and they drugged us.

862
00:46:39,862 --> 00:46:41,448
What's wrong.

863
00:46:51,241 --> 00:46:53,896
[Dr. Winslow] She won't
participate in group sessions.

864
00:46:53,965 --> 00:46:55,896
She disobeys all the rules.

865
00:46:55,965 --> 00:46:58,000
She takes no interest
in her own recovery.

866
00:46:59,965 --> 00:47:01,965
I can't believe that's Laura.

867
00:47:03,758 --> 00:47:05,068
Needless to say,

868
00:47:05,137 --> 00:47:08,344
the two week evaluation
period was a bit optimistic.

869
00:47:08,413 --> 00:47:11,275
We suggest that her stay be
extended by at least a month.

870
00:47:11,344 --> 00:47:12,965
A month?

871
00:47:13,034 --> 00:47:15,448
I-- I don't know.

872
00:47:15,517 --> 00:47:18,482
Mr. Mills, your daughter's
behavior has become volatile.

873
00:47:18,551 --> 00:47:19,827
She's a danger to herself.

874
00:47:19,896 --> 00:47:21,310
She's a danger to others.

875
00:47:21,379 --> 00:47:24,000
She requires
24-hour supervision.

876
00:47:24,068 --> 00:47:26,068
Are you prepared to watch
her for that long?

877
00:47:26,137 --> 00:47:27,862
Unless you say to me that you
know what is best

878
00:47:27,931 --> 00:47:28,896
for your daughter, then I'll--

879
00:47:28,965 --> 00:47:30,482
No.

880
00:47:30,551 --> 00:47:32,517
She'll be safer there.

881
00:47:37,689 --> 00:47:40,034
How do we get her
to understand...

882
00:47:40,103 --> 00:47:41,655
that she needs this help?

883
00:47:43,206 --> 00:47:44,241
Let me talk to her.

884
00:47:46,137 --> 00:47:47,758
[steps walking away]

885
00:47:53,068 --> 00:47:54,758
[Laura] You're not taking
me back there.

886
00:47:56,551 --> 00:48:00,344
Laura, the way I see
it you have two choices.

887
00:48:00,413 --> 00:48:02,206
You either come
back to Meadowbrook,

888
00:48:02,275 --> 00:48:05,137
without making a scene...

889
00:48:05,206 --> 00:48:07,206
or I call child services

890
00:48:07,275 --> 00:48:10,586
and you go straight to a
juvenile detention center.

891
00:48:10,655 --> 00:48:14,000
And if you were uncomfortable
at Meadowbrook, believe me...

892
00:48:15,620 --> 00:48:17,793
this is it, choice is yours.

893
00:48:20,586 --> 00:48:23,034
[door opens]

894
00:48:23,103 --> 00:48:24,965
I don't understand why
you're doing this to me.

895
00:48:25,034 --> 00:48:27,034
Everything I told you was true.

896
00:48:33,758 --> 00:48:34,931
Hey.

897
00:48:35,000 --> 00:48:36,413
Call a woman named
Nora, the Teen Law Office,

898
00:48:36,482 --> 00:48:38,137
she'll tell you everything.

899
00:48:44,034 --> 00:48:45,379
You're making
the right decision.

900
00:48:45,448 --> 00:48:46,655
Yeah.

901
00:48:50,034 --> 00:48:51,172
[engine revs]

902
00:48:51,241 --> 00:48:52,241
[van door closes]

903
00:48:58,275 --> 00:49:00,379
[sad music]

904
00:49:08,137 --> 00:49:09,206
I'm going to work.

905
00:49:13,310 --> 00:49:16,896
[defiant music]

906
00:49:33,965 --> 00:49:35,827
Wait a second, you're
not putting me in those.

907
00:49:35,896 --> 00:49:37,896
You ran away, you're
going to be strapped.

908
00:49:37,965 --> 00:49:40,068
No, let go of me!

909
00:49:41,620 --> 00:49:43,000
No! No!

910
00:49:43,068 --> 00:49:44,344
No!

911
00:49:44,413 --> 00:49:47,000
You can't do this, let me out.

912
00:49:47,068 --> 00:49:48,827
You better regulate
your moods Laura.

913
00:49:48,896 --> 00:49:50,379
No! Get that away from me.

914
00:49:50,448 --> 00:49:52,068
You'll feel better
in a few minutes.

915
00:49:53,965 --> 00:49:57,103
[panting]

916
00:49:57,172 --> 00:49:59,000
[sighs hard]

917
00:50:21,862 --> 00:50:24,000
You all right?

918
00:50:24,068 --> 00:50:26,310
I couldn't sleep.

919
00:50:26,379 --> 00:50:27,379
I feel like Judas.

920
00:50:29,448 --> 00:50:32,724
Don't think like that,
we did what we had to.

921
00:50:34,896 --> 00:50:36,103
What if she's
telling the truth

922
00:50:36,172 --> 00:50:38,241
about what goes on in there.

923
00:50:38,310 --> 00:50:39,551
You really think
kids are being drugged

924
00:50:39,620 --> 00:50:41,724
and strapped to chairs?

925
00:50:41,793 --> 00:50:44,482
What if it isn't helping,
what if it's making her worse.

926
00:50:44,551 --> 00:50:46,275
It has to work.

927
00:50:46,344 --> 00:50:48,793
It has to. Otherwise
we have lost everything

928
00:50:48,862 --> 00:50:51,034
that we've ever planned
for her, her whole future.

929
00:50:51,103 --> 00:50:52,689
All of her dreams gone.

930
00:50:54,482 --> 00:50:56,517
When did we ever ask
her what her dreams were?

931
00:51:01,896 --> 00:51:04,413
[Dr. Winslow] Laura?

932
00:51:04,482 --> 00:51:06,724
Laura?

933
00:51:06,793 --> 00:51:08,655
Hello Laura.

934
00:51:08,724 --> 00:51:10,241
How are we doing?

935
00:51:10,310 --> 00:51:13,206
I'm strapped to my bed,
how do you think I'm doing?

936
00:51:13,275 --> 00:51:16,413
Please, Laura, it doesn't
have to be this difficult.

937
00:51:16,482 --> 00:51:18,655
You don't have to fight.

938
00:51:18,724 --> 00:51:21,862
Then let me out and I won't.

939
00:51:21,931 --> 00:51:23,241
It doesn't work that way.

940
00:51:23,310 --> 00:51:25,517
You first have to acknowledge
that you have problems

941
00:51:25,586 --> 00:51:27,344
and that you need our help.

942
00:51:27,413 --> 00:51:29,413
I don't need your help.

943
00:51:29,482 --> 00:51:30,620
[panting]

944
00:51:30,689 --> 00:51:31,931
Just let me out!

945
00:51:32,000 --> 00:51:33,068
You give us no choice

946
00:51:33,137 --> 00:51:35,000
but to continue this
course of treatment

947
00:51:37,379 --> 00:51:40,448
Dr. Winslow, this patient
has had over 30 milligrams

948
00:51:40,517 --> 00:51:42,758
of Cyclizine in
the last 24 hours.

949
00:51:45,448 --> 00:51:46,758
All right. Let her rest.

950
00:51:52,068 --> 00:51:54,448
[grunting]

951
00:51:54,517 --> 00:51:57,482
[rapid door knocks]

952
00:52:05,655 --> 00:52:08,206
Hi.

953
00:52:08,275 --> 00:52:11,068
Listen. I know I'm not
supposed to be here, but...

954
00:52:11,137 --> 00:52:13,034
I just came by to see
how Laura was doing.

955
00:52:13,103 --> 00:52:14,620
Alright?

956
00:52:14,689 --> 00:52:16,206
She's not here.

957
00:52:16,275 --> 00:52:17,655
Oh yeah. Where'd she go?

958
00:52:20,551 --> 00:52:22,034
You sent her back
there, didn't you?

959
00:52:25,310 --> 00:52:27,689
I can't believe you, how
could you do that to her?

960
00:52:27,758 --> 00:52:28,862
We were afraid she
was gonna kill herself.

961
00:52:28,931 --> 00:52:30,896
We had no other choice.

962
00:52:30,965 --> 00:52:32,931
What are you babbling about?

963
00:52:33,000 --> 00:52:35,724
Laura would never kill herself.

964
00:52:35,793 --> 00:52:37,758
What are you
doing here, David?

965
00:52:37,827 --> 00:52:39,517
I told you not to set
foot in this house

966
00:52:39,586 --> 00:52:40,896
until you'd paid back--

967
00:52:40,965 --> 00:52:42,034
Don't worry, you don't have
to lock up the silverware,

968
00:52:42,103 --> 00:52:43,862
I'm leaving.

969
00:52:43,931 --> 00:52:45,620
I just came by to see my sister.

970
00:52:47,517 --> 00:52:48,827
Leave Laura alone.

971
00:52:48,896 --> 00:52:50,517
I don't want you around her.

972
00:52:50,586 --> 00:52:51,689
You've done enough.

973
00:52:51,758 --> 00:52:53,344
Ooh, really?

974
00:52:53,413 --> 00:52:55,379
Hey, I hear the mom of
the year award is coming up.

975
00:52:55,448 --> 00:52:58,068
Maybe Laura and
I will nominate you.

976
00:52:58,137 --> 00:52:59,689
Don't look at him.

977
00:52:59,758 --> 00:53:01,241
He never gets his hands dirty.
He's the man of stone--

978
00:53:01,310 --> 00:53:02,310
All right David.

979
00:53:02,379 --> 00:53:04,172
[David] Aren't you pops.

980
00:53:04,241 --> 00:53:05,482
You can leave now.

981
00:53:05,551 --> 00:53:07,206
If you think Laura's just
going to waltz back in here

982
00:53:07,275 --> 00:53:08,413
and forgive you for
what you've done,

983
00:53:08,482 --> 00:53:09,793
you're both insane.

984
00:53:09,862 --> 00:53:11,931
And you wonder why you're
not welcome in this house.

985
00:53:12,000 --> 00:53:14,413
Oh you make sure to remind
me every chance you get.

986
00:53:16,793 --> 00:53:18,068
[bangs door]

987
00:53:26,275 --> 00:53:27,103
Hi.

988
00:53:32,620 --> 00:53:33,931
Eh--

989
00:53:34,000 --> 00:53:35,793
I was just nowhere
near your neighborhood.

990
00:53:35,862 --> 00:53:37,482
And thought I stop in
for a cup of coffee.

991
00:53:37,551 --> 00:53:38,551
[laughs backwardly]

992
00:53:43,689 --> 00:53:44,724
Are you okay?

993
00:53:48,620 --> 00:53:50,206
[Marty shushing]

994
00:53:50,275 --> 00:53:53,586
Come on, don't cry.

995
00:53:53,655 --> 00:53:56,241
[Marty] Hey, do you believe
in reincarnation?

996
00:53:56,310 --> 00:53:58,448
'Cause I do.

997
00:53:58,517 --> 00:54:00,275
I believe I'm gonna
come back after I die.

998
00:54:00,344 --> 00:54:03,034
And I'm coming back
as rock star,

999
00:54:03,103 --> 00:54:06,482
Michael Jordan, something.

1000
00:54:06,551 --> 00:54:09,310
Next time, it's gonna be better.

1001
00:54:09,379 --> 00:54:10,724
So when it gets real bad,

1002
00:54:10,793 --> 00:54:12,137
you know?
you think about that.

1003
00:54:12,206 --> 00:54:14,172
Think about next time,

1004
00:54:14,241 --> 00:54:15,551
another chance.

1005
00:54:23,068 --> 00:54:25,068
Get a grip.

1006
00:54:25,137 --> 00:54:26,689
You belong in your own wing.

1007
00:54:26,758 --> 00:54:28,275
You know the rules.

1008
00:54:28,344 --> 00:54:30,827
Thank you, Dr. Winslow.
I'll modify my behavior.

1009
00:54:48,344 --> 00:54:50,931
Laura...

1010
00:54:51,000 --> 00:54:53,310
your moods have
become unmanageable.

1011
00:54:54,931 --> 00:54:57,724
You need therapeutic
intervention.

1012
00:54:57,793 --> 00:54:59,000
You can't handle
this on your own.

1013
00:54:59,068 --> 00:55:01,000
You know that now, don't you?

1014
00:55:03,655 --> 00:55:06,896
I think you're ready
to start cooperating.

1015
00:55:06,965 --> 00:55:08,000
It's time to let go.

1016
00:55:12,172 --> 00:55:15,827
You've gotten a grip on
your anger, haven't you?

1017
00:55:15,896 --> 00:55:18,758
[whispering] Yes.

1018
00:55:18,827 --> 00:55:20,000
I'm proud of you.

1019
00:55:22,724 --> 00:55:24,965
You're gonna be just fine.

1020
00:56:12,758 --> 00:56:16,000
[chattering]

1021
00:56:20,862 --> 00:56:23,034
Hey, they let you out.

1022
00:56:23,103 --> 00:56:24,413
Yeah.

1023
00:56:24,482 --> 00:56:26,034
Yeah, I don't want
any more trouble.

1024
00:56:26,103 --> 00:56:29,241
I'm just gonna do my time.

1025
00:56:29,310 --> 00:56:31,413
Tell them everything
they wanna hear.

1026
00:56:31,482 --> 00:56:33,241
Good. That's good.

1027
00:56:33,310 --> 00:56:34,689
It's easier that way.

1028
00:56:34,758 --> 00:56:38,724
Yeah. They made me a level
two for promising to cooperate.

1029
00:56:38,793 --> 00:56:39,896
[Marty chuckles]

1030
00:56:39,965 --> 00:56:42,379
Took me out of Cyclizine.

1031
00:56:42,448 --> 00:56:45,931
So then, you'll be
okay in here without me.

1032
00:56:48,034 --> 00:56:49,896
What do you mean?

1033
00:56:49,965 --> 00:56:53,344
I'm getting out today?

1034
00:56:53,413 --> 00:56:54,103
What happened?

1035
00:56:54,172 --> 00:56:55,137
I don't know.

1036
00:56:55,206 --> 00:56:56,827
They just told me
to go pack my stuff.

1037
00:56:56,896 --> 00:56:57,931
[chuckles]

1038
00:56:58,000 --> 00:56:59,137
That's great.

1039
00:56:59,206 --> 00:57:00,551
Yeah. Yeah, my dad is
going to come pick me up.

1040
00:57:00,620 --> 00:57:02,551
We're gonna go to our house
was going to be a big party.

1041
00:57:02,620 --> 00:57:05,000
Everyone's going to be there.

1042
00:57:05,068 --> 00:57:06,793
You know.
I'll give you my number.

1043
00:57:06,862 --> 00:57:08,137
Now that you're in level two.

1044
00:57:08,206 --> 00:57:09,310
You call me, right?

1045
00:57:09,379 --> 00:57:11,310
Yeah, I will, I promise.

1046
00:57:13,862 --> 00:57:15,896
You gonna be okay
out there, aren't you?

1047
00:57:15,965 --> 00:57:18,724
Me? Yes, of course.

1048
00:57:18,793 --> 00:57:20,344
I told you I'm all better.

1049
00:57:21,827 --> 00:57:23,068
Really.

1050
00:57:23,137 --> 00:57:25,137
Okay.

1051
00:57:25,206 --> 00:57:26,689
Don't forget
to take your meds.

1052
00:57:26,758 --> 00:57:28,862
Yes, I will. I promise.

1053
00:57:31,379 --> 00:57:32,827
I-- I'm going to miss you.

1054
00:57:34,827 --> 00:57:35,896
[sighs]

1055
00:57:35,965 --> 00:57:38,655
You're the only
friend I have in here.

1056
00:57:38,724 --> 00:57:41,896
We'll still be friends.

1057
00:57:41,965 --> 00:57:44,000
We'll always be friends.

1058
00:58:01,689 --> 00:58:03,551
[sighs]

1059
00:58:09,896 --> 00:58:11,172
-[Robert] Hi.
-[Woman] Yeah?

1060
00:58:11,241 --> 00:58:13,758
-[Nora] What do you want?
-[Robert] Are you Nora Fields?

1061
00:58:13,827 --> 00:58:15,275
Last time I looked.

1062
00:58:15,344 --> 00:58:17,620
I-- I talked to your
secretary earlier.

1063
00:58:17,689 --> 00:58:19,000
My name is Robert Mills.

1064
00:58:19,068 --> 00:58:20,034
I got your name
from my daughter.

1065
00:58:20,103 --> 00:58:21,413
She's a...

1066
00:58:21,482 --> 00:58:22,965
patient...

1067
00:58:23,034 --> 00:58:24,034
at Meadowbrook,

1068
00:58:24,103 --> 00:58:25,586
which is an adolescent
treatment center.

1069
00:58:25,655 --> 00:58:28,758
I know what it is. Sit down.

1070
00:58:28,827 --> 00:58:30,793
How'd your daughter get my name.

1071
00:58:30,862 --> 00:58:32,103
I don't know.

1072
00:58:32,172 --> 00:58:34,413
But she told me that you
knew all about these places.

1073
00:58:34,482 --> 00:58:35,793
Is that true?

1074
00:58:35,862 --> 00:58:37,793
I advocate for kids who
have been wrongly placed

1075
00:58:37,862 --> 00:58:39,551
in institutions
like Meadowbrook,

1076
00:58:39,620 --> 00:58:42,689
which you might
if you're like most of them.

1077
00:58:42,758 --> 00:58:45,896
That's not to say there
aren't some good ones.

1078
00:58:45,965 --> 00:58:49,551
There are, but I'm here
for the ones that aren't.

1079
00:58:49,620 --> 00:58:51,620
I'm with this little...

1080
00:58:51,689 --> 00:58:53,793
David and Goliath thing here,
you know.

1081
00:58:53,862 --> 00:58:55,724
Just glad it's me
and my secretary.

1082
00:58:57,586 --> 00:59:00,241
for the whole operation,
so, I'm clearly insane.

1083
00:59:01,758 --> 00:59:02,620
Herbal... disgusting.

1084
00:59:05,344 --> 00:59:08,620
So, what can I do
for you Mr. Mills?

1085
00:59:10,206 --> 00:59:11,103
Eh--

1086
00:59:11,172 --> 00:59:13,103
My daughter, Laura

1087
00:59:13,172 --> 00:59:15,310
tried to tell us that there are
some pretty awful things

1088
00:59:15,379 --> 00:59:16,758
that go on in these places.

1089
00:59:16,827 --> 00:59:18,931
And...

1090
00:59:19,000 --> 00:59:20,758
to be honest with you,
I don't know what to believe.

1091
00:59:22,689 --> 00:59:26,103
Well, if half of what you
said was true, is that enough?

1092
00:59:27,965 --> 00:59:30,551
Yeah, I guess it would be.

1093
00:59:30,620 --> 00:59:32,172
I guess you got your answer.

1094
00:59:32,241 --> 00:59:33,103
Well...

1095
00:59:33,172 --> 00:59:34,206
let's hope for her sake

1096
00:59:34,275 --> 00:59:36,586
that you got a lousy
insurance policy.

1097
00:59:36,655 --> 00:59:39,103
I'm sorry, I don't understand.

1098
00:59:39,172 --> 00:59:40,827
Now you see the length
of stay in these place,

1099
00:59:40,896 --> 00:59:43,758
seems to depend on how much
the insurance will cover.

1100
00:59:43,827 --> 00:59:47,275
Insurance runs out, presto
change-o, Johnny's cured.

1101
00:59:47,344 --> 00:59:49,103
Well, how can they do that?
That's not right.

1102
00:59:49,172 --> 00:59:50,655
[scoffs]

1103
00:59:50,724 --> 00:59:52,137
Mr. Mills,

1104
00:59:52,206 --> 00:59:53,965
would you buy a car
without checking it out first?

1105
00:59:54,034 --> 00:59:56,862
I mean, at least
kicking the tires.

1106
00:59:56,931 --> 00:59:58,241
No, of course not.

1107
01:00:00,068 --> 01:00:03,413
I hate to tell you this,
but you just bought a lemon.

1108
01:00:03,482 --> 01:00:04,655
What do you mean?

1109
01:00:07,068 --> 01:00:08,931
Did they give you a
tour of Meadowbrook?

1110
01:00:17,413 --> 01:00:18,965
[Robert shuffles on his seat]

1111
01:00:19,034 --> 01:00:22,517
All right Mr. Mills, I'm
gonna tell you a little bit

1112
01:00:22,586 --> 01:00:24,620
about these private
treatment facilities.

1113
01:00:48,482 --> 01:00:52,275
[sad music]

1114
01:00:58,448 --> 01:01:00,827
[smile]

1115
01:01:03,413 --> 01:01:05,482
[sobbing]

1116
01:01:07,896 --> 01:01:09,517
[sighs]

1117
01:01:22,000 --> 01:01:23,724
[CJ] Hey, they don't like
you to stay in here

1118
01:01:23,793 --> 01:01:25,275
after the social hour.

1119
01:01:26,758 --> 01:01:29,827
Thanks.

1120
01:01:29,896 --> 01:01:32,379
So, did you get in
trouble after the fire alarm?

1121
01:01:32,448 --> 01:01:35,379
That? No, a couple of
days in SR, no big deal.

1122
01:01:37,965 --> 01:01:39,241
Sorry.

1123
01:01:39,310 --> 01:01:40,896
Forget it. You would've done
the same for me, right?

1124
01:01:44,379 --> 01:01:45,931
Listen, you have to stop
getting the injections

1125
01:01:46,000 --> 01:01:48,758
once they got you hooked
on the big T you're theirs.

1126
01:01:48,827 --> 01:01:50,482
I'm not getting
injections anymore.

1127
01:01:50,551 --> 01:01:52,310
They're just giving
me a couple pills.

1128
01:01:52,379 --> 01:01:55,344
Good. You have to
start cheeking them.

1129
01:01:55,413 --> 01:01:58,517
Why do you care
what happens to me?

1130
01:01:58,586 --> 01:02:00,103
I just do that sometimes.

1131
01:02:01,965 --> 01:02:03,137
Come on.

1132
01:02:17,103 --> 01:02:19,413
I went to see someone today,

1133
01:02:19,482 --> 01:02:22,000
a woman from the
Teen Law Office.

1134
01:02:25,379 --> 01:02:27,034
I think Laura was
telling the truth

1135
01:02:27,103 --> 01:02:29,965
about the things that
go on in that place.

1136
01:02:30,034 --> 01:02:32,482
Why are you doing this?

1137
01:02:32,551 --> 01:02:35,068
She needs to be there to
be watched 24 hours a day.

1138
01:02:35,137 --> 01:02:37,655
These places like
Meadowbrook are dumping grounds

1139
01:02:37,724 --> 01:02:39,758
for parents looking
for easy answers.

1140
01:02:39,827 --> 01:02:41,034
Easy answers?

1141
01:02:41,103 --> 01:02:42,482
There's a lot of kids that
don't even belong there.

1142
01:02:42,551 --> 01:02:45,862
Th-- This woman, she was telling
me that these hospitals,

1143
01:02:45,931 --> 01:02:48,068
they overcharge and
double building insurance

1144
01:02:48,137 --> 01:02:49,275
until they bleed them dry.

1145
01:02:49,344 --> 01:02:51,103
And then they stamp
cured on the kid's file

1146
01:02:51,172 --> 01:02:52,172
and turn them loose.

1147
01:02:52,241 --> 01:02:53,103
That's not happening
at Meadowbrook.

1148
01:02:53,172 --> 01:02:54,310
We were there.

1149
01:02:54,379 --> 01:02:55,827
Honey, I think we gotta
get her out of there

1150
01:02:55,896 --> 01:02:58,103
and into some kind
of family counseling.

1151
01:02:58,172 --> 01:02:59,620
[Michelle sighs heavily]

1152
01:02:59,689 --> 01:03:01,448
You always do this to me.

1153
01:03:01,517 --> 01:03:03,827
We take a stand together
and then you fold

1154
01:03:03,896 --> 01:03:05,896
and I'm left picking
up the pieces.

1155
01:03:05,965 --> 01:03:06,931
If it weren't for me,

1156
01:03:07,000 --> 01:03:08,172
nothing would get
done in this family.

1157
01:03:08,241 --> 01:03:10,172
Hey, I work my off every day.

1158
01:03:10,241 --> 01:03:11,655
-[Michelle] And I don't?
-[Robert] I didn't say that.

1159
01:03:11,724 --> 01:03:13,034
You know, if you had been there,

1160
01:03:13,103 --> 01:03:14,896
if you had been available
for your children,

1161
01:03:14,965 --> 01:03:17,551
if you would've been willing
to take a stand just once,

1162
01:03:17,620 --> 01:03:19,482
we wouldn't be in this mess.

1163
01:03:19,551 --> 01:03:21,655
I have a responsibility
to my child.

1164
01:03:21,724 --> 01:03:23,172
She needs me to
be strong for her

1165
01:03:23,241 --> 01:03:24,827
and I'm going to be strong.

1166
01:03:24,896 --> 01:03:25,724
Where are you going?

1167
01:03:25,793 --> 01:03:26,896
Out.

1168
01:03:59,137 --> 01:04:00,724
[door knocks]

1169
01:04:19,310 --> 01:04:21,551
-[Robert]
-Hi.

1170
01:04:21,620 --> 01:04:23,551
I was wondering
if we could talk.

1171
01:04:26,551 --> 01:04:28,793
Yeah. It's late.

1172
01:04:28,862 --> 01:04:32,103
I know. I thought maybe
we could get a beer.

1173
01:04:36,724 --> 01:04:38,137
Sure.

1174
01:04:38,206 --> 01:04:39,448
As long as
it's non-alcoholic.

1175
01:04:55,896 --> 01:04:59,034
I heard Stewart's
dad gave you a job.

1176
01:04:59,103 --> 01:05:01,896
Yeah, they got a big
contract with the city.

1177
01:05:01,965 --> 01:05:04,206
Need an extra hand.

1178
01:05:04,275 --> 01:05:05,379
It's nothing much,

1179
01:05:05,448 --> 01:05:06,827
it's just got me doing
some groundwork for now.

1180
01:05:06,896 --> 01:05:09,034
Mostly sub-metering, three-phase
wiring, stuff like that.

1181
01:05:09,103 --> 01:05:10,827
Oh, that's great.

1182
01:05:16,103 --> 01:05:17,379
Look...

1183
01:05:17,448 --> 01:05:19,241
I know you didn't bring me
here to talk about my job.

1184
01:05:22,068 --> 01:05:24,724
I know you brought
Laura home the other day.

1185
01:05:24,793 --> 01:05:26,758
But David, I need to know
did she say anything

1186
01:05:26,827 --> 01:05:28,517
about what goes
on in that place?

1187
01:05:31,172 --> 01:05:33,034
Yeah, she did.

1188
01:05:33,103 --> 01:05:34,620
Sound like a concentration
camp in there.

1189
01:05:34,689 --> 01:05:36,448
And you believe her?

1190
01:05:36,517 --> 01:05:37,586
She wouldn't lie to me.

1191
01:05:39,448 --> 01:05:40,965
[sighs hard]

1192
01:05:41,034 --> 01:05:42,758
We really trying to do
what we thought was best.

1193
01:05:42,827 --> 01:05:45,310
She thought it was best?

1194
01:05:45,379 --> 01:05:46,689
Wait til she gets
out of that place.

1195
01:05:46,758 --> 01:05:47,896
And she has to go back to school

1196
01:05:47,965 --> 01:05:51,310
where everyone knows
she was in a nuthouse.

1197
01:05:51,379 --> 01:05:52,413
It's getting late....

1198
01:05:52,482 --> 01:05:53,413
No. Wait, wait, Please.

1199
01:06:00,241 --> 01:06:03,620
Look, I didn't kind of
just talk about Laura. I--

1200
01:06:03,689 --> 01:06:05,620
I came because I
needed to talk to you.

1201
01:06:08,172 --> 01:06:11,379
Look, David. I know how
hard this has been for you.

1202
01:06:11,448 --> 01:06:14,482
It hasn't been
any easier for me.

1203
01:06:14,551 --> 01:06:16,586
Your mother and I, we
haven't said two civil words

1204
01:06:16,655 --> 01:06:17,724
to each other since you left.

1205
01:06:17,793 --> 01:06:18,896
So it's my fault then?

1206
01:06:18,965 --> 01:06:20,896
No, no, no.

1207
01:06:20,965 --> 01:06:24,034
I have no one to
blame, but myself,

1208
01:06:24,103 --> 01:06:27,137
I know I haven't been
the perfect husband

1209
01:06:27,206 --> 01:06:28,068
or the perfect father.

1210
01:06:34,000 --> 01:06:36,517
But I'd still like to
think that you and I could...

1211
01:06:36,586 --> 01:06:38,827
[chuckles]

1212
01:06:38,896 --> 01:06:40,482
It's a little late for
you to try and be my dad.

1213
01:06:40,551 --> 01:06:42,931
Don't you think?

1214
01:06:43,000 --> 01:06:44,068
I mean, it's not like
we're going to go

1215
01:06:44,137 --> 01:06:45,724
in the backyard and chuck
the old football around.

1216
01:06:55,344 --> 01:06:56,517
Yeah, you're right.

1217
01:07:01,896 --> 01:07:04,724
But I'm still your father

1218
01:07:04,793 --> 01:07:06,344
and I love you.

1219
01:07:06,413 --> 01:07:07,758
[sighs]

1220
01:07:07,827 --> 01:07:09,551
Look, do you want me to
let you off the hook?

1221
01:07:09,620 --> 01:07:11,379
Fine. You're off the hook.

1222
01:07:11,448 --> 01:07:13,068
I screwed up, I know that.

1223
01:07:13,137 --> 01:07:15,758
Living with me was no picnic
either,

1224
01:07:15,827 --> 01:07:17,413
but I'm okay now.

1225
01:07:17,482 --> 01:07:18,586
I'm not carrying any grudges.

1226
01:07:18,655 --> 01:07:20,103
Things just turned out
the way they turned out.

1227
01:07:20,172 --> 01:07:22,620
You know, end of story.

1228
01:07:22,689 --> 01:07:25,310
So you can just stop feeling
sorry for yourself, okay?

1229
01:07:29,689 --> 01:07:31,172
Thanks for the soda.

1230
01:07:55,172 --> 01:07:56,275
Hey, come on.

1231
01:07:56,344 --> 01:07:57,827
Let's go back to your room.

1232
01:07:59,413 --> 01:08:02,103
[Laura] Come on.

1233
01:08:02,172 --> 01:08:04,000
everything's gonna be okay.

1234
01:08:08,655 --> 01:08:10,310
You all right?

1235
01:08:10,379 --> 01:08:13,379
Come on,
let's just lie down.

1236
01:08:13,448 --> 01:08:15,000
Come on.

1237
01:08:20,206 --> 01:08:22,137
[door creaking]

1238
01:08:24,517 --> 01:08:26,000
What are you doing here?

1239
01:08:26,068 --> 01:08:28,275
Maybe I should ask
you the same thing.

1240
01:08:28,344 --> 01:08:30,758
Listen, don't let
no one come in please.

1241
01:08:30,827 --> 01:08:33,862
Fine, tell me what
you're doing in there.

1242
01:08:33,931 --> 01:08:35,551
Why don't we just
go back to our rooms

1243
01:08:35,620 --> 01:08:37,689
and forget about
everything, okay?

1244
01:08:37,758 --> 01:08:40,413
Come on. The attendee
comes by 40 seconds.

1245
01:08:40,482 --> 01:08:41,517
Fine.

1246
01:08:43,413 --> 01:08:45,344
Thanks.

1247
01:08:45,413 --> 01:08:46,482
Now we're even.

1248
01:09:01,689 --> 01:09:04,172
Open.

1249
01:09:04,241 --> 01:09:05,310
Tongue?

1250
01:09:07,137 --> 01:09:08,620
I'm proud of the way
you've been taking

1251
01:09:08,689 --> 01:09:10,275
your medication lately.

1252
01:09:10,344 --> 01:09:13,034
You've just earned
yourself another 10 points.

1253
01:09:23,379 --> 01:09:25,586
[Counselor] It's nice to have
you joining us again Laura.

1254
01:09:25,655 --> 01:09:28,551
I don't suppose you're ready
to start participating.

1255
01:09:34,379 --> 01:09:35,862
My name's Laura

1256
01:09:35,931 --> 01:09:38,862
and I'm an alcoholic.

1257
01:09:38,931 --> 01:09:40,482
No, listen.

1258
01:09:40,551 --> 01:09:43,551
I've told you a hundred
times, I cannot do it anymore.

1259
01:09:43,620 --> 01:09:45,172
That's it.

1260
01:09:46,827 --> 01:09:49,310
I know, I know, I
know, I'm sorry.

1261
01:09:49,379 --> 01:09:51,758
Look, it's my fault.

1262
01:09:51,827 --> 01:09:54,827
I guess I have to
get it together.

1263
01:09:54,896 --> 01:09:56,344
I have a family.

1264
01:09:56,413 --> 01:09:58,862
I gotta start being
there for my kids.

1265
01:09:58,931 --> 01:10:00,793
You know?

1266
01:10:00,862 --> 01:10:02,827
No, I'm sorry.

1267
01:10:02,896 --> 01:10:04,172
It's over.

1268
01:10:04,241 --> 01:10:05,275
That's it.

1269
01:10:11,206 --> 01:10:12,724
Oh.

1270
01:10:12,793 --> 01:10:15,103
Mr. Mills.

1271
01:10:15,172 --> 01:10:16,655
What can I do for you?

1272
01:10:16,724 --> 01:10:19,620
Well, I've come to get Laura.

1273
01:10:19,689 --> 01:10:20,724
Yes. Is there a problem?

1274
01:10:20,793 --> 01:10:22,103
No, no, no, no.
There is no problem.

1275
01:10:22,172 --> 01:10:23,310
We just want her at home.

1276
01:10:23,379 --> 01:10:25,137
We, is your wife here?

1277
01:10:25,206 --> 01:10:26,310
No, she couldn't come.

1278
01:10:26,379 --> 01:10:29,137
I see, have a seat.

1279
01:10:29,206 --> 01:10:30,275
[Robert clears throat]
No, that's all right.

1280
01:10:30,344 --> 01:10:32,689
I think I'll stand.

1281
01:10:32,758 --> 01:10:34,724
Mr. Mills, it is not advisable

1282
01:10:34,793 --> 01:10:35,965
for you to take
Laura out of here

1283
01:10:36,034 --> 01:10:37,620
before her treatment
is complete.

1284
01:10:37,689 --> 01:10:39,103
Just show me where to sign.

1285
01:10:39,172 --> 01:10:41,103
I'm afraid it's not that easy.

1286
01:10:41,172 --> 01:10:43,310
We have been authorized
by you, her legal guardian

1287
01:10:43,379 --> 01:10:46,758
and your insurance company
to perform a service.

1288
01:10:46,827 --> 01:10:50,241
We have diagnosed her as
being severely depressed.

1289
01:10:50,310 --> 01:10:54,448
That's enough to mandate a
stay here for up to six months.

1290
01:10:54,517 --> 01:10:56,620
Six months?

1291
01:10:56,689 --> 01:10:58,241
What are you talking about?

1292
01:11:00,586 --> 01:11:04,206
Let me try to explain
this as simply as I can.

1293
01:11:04,275 --> 01:11:07,517
If you take Laura out of
here against medical advice

1294
01:11:07,586 --> 01:11:10,965
and she harms herself, you
could be liable for negligence.

1295
01:11:11,034 --> 01:11:13,000
You could lose custody
of your daughter.

1296
