It's just ridiculous.

1551
01:25:09,724 --> 01:25:12,000
I'm not gonna wait for them.

1552
01:25:15,275 --> 01:25:18,241
I want you to go get Laura,
we haven't got all day.

1553
01:25:18,310 --> 01:25:20,965
I don't know if I can do that.

1554
01:25:21,034 --> 01:25:22,620
Oh, I think you can.

1555
01:25:46,103 --> 01:25:48,758
[Ms. Collins] Dr. Winslow...

1556
01:25:48,827 --> 01:25:50,586
her parents
won't wait any longer.

1557
01:25:50,655 --> 01:25:52,000
All right. Take her out.
I won't be long.

1558
01:26:06,103 --> 01:26:08,689
[Nurse]
Dr. Winslow, the ward is clear.

1559
01:26:16,965 --> 01:26:19,482
Dr. Winslow.

1560
01:26:19,551 --> 01:26:21,172
You dropped this.

1561
01:26:29,965 --> 01:26:32,689
[dramatic music]

1562
01:26:48,310 --> 01:26:50,172
Ms. Collins!

1563
01:26:50,241 --> 01:26:51,896
[grunts]

1564
01:26:51,965 --> 01:26:53,241
[Ms. Collins] Come on! Get her!

1565
01:26:53,310 --> 01:26:54,724
-[Robert] Come on--
-[Laura] Dad!

1566
01:26:54,793 --> 01:26:56,137
Dad! Get off me!

1567
01:26:56,206 --> 01:26:57,275
[Robert] Laura!

1568
01:26:58,655 --> 01:27:00,000
[Dr. Winslow] Calm down.

1569
01:27:00,068 --> 01:27:00,965
[Laura] Let me go!

1570
01:27:01,034 --> 01:27:02,172
[Dr. Winslow] Calm down.

1571
01:27:02,241 --> 01:27:03,275
Let me go.

1572
01:27:03,344 --> 01:27:05,448
Laura, don't make a scene.

1573
01:27:05,517 --> 01:27:06,517
She doesn't have it!

1574
01:27:06,586 --> 01:27:07,965
Let her go or
I'll call the police.

1575
01:27:08,034 --> 01:27:09,344
[Dr. Winslow] We have reason to
believe that your daughter

1576
01:27:09,413 --> 01:27:11,172
is hiding drugs in her room.

1577
01:27:11,241 --> 01:27:13,103
He's lying I don't know
what he's talking about.

1578
01:27:13,172 --> 01:27:14,551
We're taking our
daughter over here.

1579
01:27:14,620 --> 01:27:17,413
Now this patient has a
borderline personality disorder.

1580
01:27:17,482 --> 01:27:20,241
She is a danger to herself
and to everyone around her.

1581
01:27:20,310 --> 01:27:21,724
Dr. Winslow, I want to see CJ.

1582
01:27:21,793 --> 01:27:23,620
If you take her out of here now
you're going to be liable--

1583
01:27:23,689 --> 01:27:25,275
Dr. Winslow!

1584
01:27:25,344 --> 01:27:27,655
We have a warrant to
search these premises.

1585
01:27:29,827 --> 01:27:31,379
What the hell was that
all about anyway?

1586
01:27:31,448 --> 01:27:33,448
It's a long story,
I'll tell you later.

1587
01:27:39,413 --> 01:27:42,379
I don't know what to
say, these things happen.

1588
01:27:42,448 --> 01:27:43,517
Thank you.

1589
01:27:43,586 --> 01:27:44,896
Thanks.

1590
01:27:47,689 --> 01:27:49,000
Yes!

1591
01:28:46,931 --> 01:28:48,344
You're about ready?

1592
01:28:48,413 --> 01:28:50,172
Yeah, almost.

1593
01:28:50,241 --> 01:28:51,724
You might wanna leave
some of this stuff.

1594
01:28:51,793 --> 01:28:52,724
My place ain't that big.

1595
01:28:52,793 --> 01:28:55,000
[Laura chuckles]

1596
01:28:55,068 --> 01:28:56,965
[David sighs]

1597
01:28:58,965 --> 01:29:01,931
Folks getting along any better?

1598
01:29:02,000 --> 01:29:03,379
They're trying.

1599
01:29:06,172 --> 01:29:08,413
So what's the verdict
on the college thing?

1600
01:29:10,931 --> 01:29:12,103
I just told 'em

1601
01:29:12,172 --> 01:29:13,896
that I needed some time
to sort things out.

1602
01:29:13,965 --> 01:29:15,241
Maybe I'll go next year.

1603
01:29:18,068 --> 01:29:19,413
[grunts]

1604
01:29:19,482 --> 01:29:20,689
All right. Let's do it.

1605
01:29:31,655 --> 01:29:33,206
[Michelle] You have everything?

1606
01:29:33,275 --> 01:29:34,344
Yeah.

1607
01:29:34,413 --> 01:29:35,655
Did you want to take your TV?

1608
01:29:35,724 --> 01:29:38,655
No need still got the
one I stole from you guys.

1609
01:29:38,724 --> 01:29:40,448
Right.

1610
01:29:40,517 --> 01:29:41,827
[Robert sighs]

1611
01:29:45,241 --> 01:29:49,344
So Laura, just wanna make
sure that you know that...

1612
01:29:49,413 --> 01:29:50,931
your father and I
don't want you to go.

1613
01:29:51,000 --> 01:29:52,482
Mom, leave it alone,
it's her decision.

1614
01:29:52,551 --> 01:29:53,482
I'm telling her how I feel.

1615
01:29:53,551 --> 01:29:54,517
[David]
Mom, it's her decision--

1616
01:29:54,586 --> 01:29:55,655
[Michelle]
I'm telling her how--

1617
01:29:55,724 --> 01:29:56,793
Every time is going to
be like that?

1618
01:29:56,862 --> 01:29:58,517
Will you guys please
just stop fighting?

1619
01:29:58,586 --> 01:29:59,724
[sighs heavily]

1620
01:30:02,103 --> 01:30:03,068
[sighs]
Let's get out of here.

1621
01:30:03,137 --> 01:30:04,310
[Robert]
Wait, wait, wait, wait.

1622
01:30:06,655 --> 01:30:08,827
This is ridiculous.

1623
01:30:08,896 --> 01:30:10,931
You're right.

1624
01:30:11,000 --> 01:30:12,586
I don't want to fight anymore.

1625
01:30:12,655 --> 01:30:14,448
We've all made
a lot of mistakes.

1626
01:30:19,000 --> 01:30:19,827
We love you.

1627
01:30:23,310 --> 01:30:24,413
Um...

1628
01:30:26,103 --> 01:30:28,310
Maybe you can come by
for dinner this weekend.

1629
01:30:31,931 --> 01:30:33,310
Both of you.

1630
01:30:36,965 --> 01:30:38,413
Mom's cooking.

1631
01:30:38,482 --> 01:30:39,517
[chuckles]

1632
01:30:45,689 --> 01:30:47,310
Could be dangerous.

1633
01:30:52,896 --> 01:30:54,551
I think we'd like that.

1634
01:30:56,551 --> 01:30:58,793
[smiles]

1635
01:30:58,862 --> 01:30:59,896
Bye.

